                      King of the silver screen                    Perhaps the only superstar of Bengali cinema and the most popular Bengali film actor ever, Uttam Kumar continues to captivate the imagination of Bengali movie-lovers even today, nearly three decades since he passed away. Uttam Kumars hypnotic screen presence, mellow voice, unique charisma and dazzling smile made him not just a heartthrob, a legend of Bengali cinema as well. For the Bengali fraternity, he is undoubtedly a mahanayak (the great hero), the undisputed king of the Bengali silver screen. To mark the matinee idols 83rd birth anniversary, Shilpi Samsad presents a programme in aid of needy artistes. Veteran actor Deepti Ray and music great Biman Mukhopadhyay will be felicitated. Also, Mahanayak Uttam Mancha hosts an evening of music and reminiscences in celebration of the evergreen heros birthday. Participants in both programmes include his grandchildren along with Supriya Devi, Goutam Ghose, Madhabi Mukhopadhyay, Tapas Paul, Nirmala Misra, Banasree Sengupta, Shatabdi Roy, Chinmoy Roy, Alpana Bandyopadhyay, Sabitri Chattopadhyay, Ramkumar Chattopadhyay, Madhuri Chattopadhyay, Srikanto Acharya, Sreela Majumder, Sreeradha Bandyopadhyay, Kalyani Mondal, Haimanti Shukla, Swagatalakshmi Dasgupta and a host of other actors, playback singers and artistes connected with the Bengali film industry.                  Event: Uttam Kumars birth anniversary programmes When: Today at 5 pm Where: Rabindra Sadan and Uttam Mancha	                    
